On 4/7/03 10:52 AM, "Sage Green" <honey_bus(-at-)hotmail.com> wrote:

> I have a small engine analyzer that measures 'point resistance'.

It checks how good the connection from the points to ground is.

From the web, "Turn the engine over until the points are closed and then use
an ohmmeter to connect the meter to the primary point lead and to ground. If
resistance reading is too high, the points are burned and must be replaced".

